// MermaidPreview
// Interactive Mermaid diagram preview with zoom, pan, and edit-mode click
// handling. Renders SVG via mermaid.render and supports center/fitToView
// commands exposed via an imperative ref (previewRef).

Zoom range: 25–400%. Pan via middle-click drag or Shift+left-drag.
Ctrl/Cmd+scroll wheel zooms in/out. Shift key shows grab cursor.
Edit mode enables clicking on .node and .edgePath DOM elements to fire
onNodeClick/onEdgeClick callbacks.

FUNCTION MermaidPreview(content, zoomLevel, onZoomIn, onZoomOut, onSetZoom, editMode, ...) -> JSX  EXPORT
  Exposes center() and fitToView() via useImperativeHandle on previewRef.
  Calls renderDiagram whenever content or theme changes.
  Renders a three-level container: outer (scroll zoom), wrapper (pan),
  inner (SVG + CSS transform with translate + scale).

---

FUNCTION center() -> void
  Resets panOffset to {0,0}. Calls onSetZoom(100).

---

FUNCTION fitToView() -> void
  Measures the rendered SVG bounding box vs wrapper dimensions.
  Calculates scale to fit, clamps to 25–400%.
  Resets pan and calls onSetZoom with the new level.

---

FUNCTION handleWheel(e) -> void
  IF Ctrl or Cmd held: calls onZoomIn or onZoomOut depending on deltaY sign.
  Prevents default scroll.

---

FUNCTION handleMouseDown(e) -> void
  Starts panning on middle-click or Shift+left-click. Captures pointer.

---

FUNCTION handleMouseMove(e) -> void
  IF panning: updates panOffset by the pointer delta.

---

FUNCTION handleMouseUp(e) -> void
  Ends panning. Releases pointer capture.

---

FUNCTION handleContextMenu(e) -> void
  Prevents the browser context menu while a pan is in progress.

---

FUNCTION handleKeyDown(e) -> void
  Sets isShiftHeld=true when Shift is pressed (shows grab cursor).

---

FUNCTION handleKeyUp(e) -> void
  Clears isShiftHeld when Shift is released.

---

FUNCTION handleDiagramClick(e) -> void
  Only active in editMode. Walks DOM ancestors looking for data-id on
  .node or .edgePath elements. Calls onNodeClick or onEdgeClick accordingly.

---

FUNCTION handleClick(e) -> void
  Only active when onNodeClickWithPosition/onEdgeClickWithPosition props are
  provided. Uses extractNodeId/extractEdgeInfo from diagramUtils to identify
  clicked elements. Calls the appropriate with-position callback.

---

FUNCTION renderDiagram() -> void
  Async. Calls initializeMermaid with current theme settings.
  Calls mermaid.render with a timestamp-suffixed unique ID.
  Sets inner container innerHTML to the resulting SVG string.
